{
  "abstract": "Linkage analysis of two linked mutant loci controlling leaf\r\nnecrosis (nec) and glabrous shoot (gl) was done with\r\neleven isozyme loci in two F2 populations of chickpea\r\n(Cicer arietinum L.). The nee and gl loci were located\r\nclosely linked to the isozyme locus Amy, 6.2 ± 1.8 cM\r\nand 15.4 ± 2.8 cM apart respectively, in a gene order of\r\nAmy-nec-gl. As the locus Amy is known to be located\r\non linkage group VII, nec and gl loci were also assigned\r\nto this linkage group. The isozyme AMY can be used\r\nas marker for necrosis gene in segregating generations.",
